        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">(Copy.)</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>23 April 5610</date>
            </p>
            <p>Reverend and Dear Sir/</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In reply to the commu-<lb/>nication in which you convey to us your
                desire<lb/> of becoming a candidate for the office of Hazan<lb/> to the Portuguese
                congregation of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, we<lb/> have to inform you that
                at a meeting held this<lb/> day, it was unanimously resolved to convey to<lb/> you
                our full concurrence in the step you propose<lb/> taking, and our best wishes for
                your success.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">At the same time, we would express the deep<lb/> regret your
                communication has afforded us showing<lb/> as it did for the first time, there
                existed a proba-<lb/>bility of our losing your valuable services, which<lb/> during
                a period of four years have given unmitiga<lb/>ted satisfaction to the whole of the
                congregation<lb/> With an earnest wish to do every thing in our<lb/> power that
                might lead to advance your interests,<lb/> and desirous of seeing you placed in that
                extend<lb/>ed sphere of usefulness the high order of your<lb/> talents
                unquestionably deserve, but which our<lb/>
                <sic>comparitively</sic> small congregation does not afford<lb/> still cannot we but
                recollect that should you<lb/> be the successful candidate we will lose one<lb/> who
                by his conduct both in public and private<lb/> life, has gained the love and respect
                of every<lb/> member of his congregation, and who by his</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>attainments, feelings, and department, we are<lb/> proud to say, has commanded the
                esteem and<lb/> respect of our Christian fellow citizens, and ac-<lb/>quired a
                reputation and position not inferior<lb/> to any of their clergy</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We would further, Reverend Sir, express<lb/> our regret at the
                prospect of being deprived,<lb/> ourselves of the advantage of your able and<lb/>
                eloquent expositions of our holy religion, and<lb/> our children of your useful and
                acceptable<lb/> Instructions in the language and faith of<lb/> our ancestors; the
                school you have established<lb/> we shall ever regard as a memento of your<lb/>
                untiring zeal and abilities.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In conclusion, dear sir, we would inform<lb/> you that under any
                circumstances your present<lb/> situation will remain open for you; and
                express<lb/>ing our best wishes for your success and ad<lb/>vancement in life, and
                although perhaps con-<lb/>trary to your wishes, hoping we may not so<lb/> soon be
                deprived of your valuable services<lb/> of which any congregation may be proud.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">We remain Reverend and Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Your obedient Servants</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Samuel Benjamin</persName> President</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">John Levey</persName> Treasurer</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Wm Benjamin</persName> Secretary</p>
            <p><persName role="author">A H David</persName> M. D.</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">G I Ascher</persName>
            </p>
            <p><persName role="author">David Moss</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways between the columns of names.">Trustees</p>
            <p>To the <addressee>Rev. Abraham De Sola</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>(The original of the present letter is<lb/> in the possession of <persName>A Hart
                    Esqr</persName><lb/> Parnass K. K. Mikveh Israel.‚Äù)</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
